<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>James M. Mudge was a newspaper reporter and columnist for the <title render="italic">Grand Rapids Herald</title>. He later became bureau chief for the <title render="italic">Detroit Free Press</title>, and press aide to Congressmen Gerald R. Ford and Guy Vander Jagt.</p>
</bioghist>



<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The collection consists primarily of clippings of newspaper articles and columns. In addition there is a scattering of correspondence, certificates, and drafts of speeches. Many of the articles relate to Detroit Mayor Jerome Cavanagh, especially his campaign for U.S. Senate in 1966. Correspondents include: Robert Griffin, John B. Swainson and G. Mennen Williams.</p>
</scopecontent>

